African soccer tournament CEDEAO 2015 (Conseil Economique, Délégué et d’Emahagement de l’Afrique Occidentale), which was hosted by city Conakry and all submetropolis. As a result of Tropical Cyclone, which hit city capital in 1993, annual revenue of Conakry dropped down with 20%, accounting to $1100. There are malnutrition and epidemics of cholera, but positive aspects are the economic growth in 6%, lowering of the poverty rate, and debt cancellation. In order to cope with economic situation and face problems faced by the country, Guinea has established Intergovernmental Framework Agreement. Actually, Intergovernmental Framework Agreement, approved on 5th of November 1994 by African Invest Bank, was made to maintain the stability of the country.

Current Situation

Political structure of Guinea is divided into several levels such as municipality, district, area, commune and lower-level province such as Lélkéla. 33 municipalities are included in the structure, and 1 local government is divided into 36 administrative areas. Guinea’s administration is not centralized system while municipalities are municipalities within municipalities. The Central Government announced Local Government Reform (LilGReform) on 31st of December 2013, and enforced on 31st of December 2014 with its goals of decentralization, improvement of public goods, empowerment of local government, and service delivery.
